# Bundle

The Bundle resource lets you create and manage bundled JavaScript/TypeScript files using [esbuild](https://esbuild.github.io/).

# Minimal Example

Bundle a TypeScript file into JavaScript.

```ts
import { Bundle } from "alchemy/esbuild";

const bundle = await Bundle("handler", {
  entryPoint: "src/handler.ts",
  outdir: ".alchemy/.out"
});
```

# Bundle for Node.js

Bundle a TypeScript file optimized for Node.js with ESM format.

```ts
import { Bundle } from "alchemy/esbuild";

const bundle = await Bundle("api", {
  entryPoint: "src/api.ts", 
  outdir: ".alchemy/.out",
  format: "esm",
  platform: "node",
  target: "node18"
});
```

# Bundle for Browser

Bundle a TypeScript file optimized for browser deployment with minification and sourcemaps.

```ts
import { Bundle } from "alchemy/esbuild";

const bundle = await Bundle("app", {
  entryPoint: "src/app.ts",
  outdir: "dist",
  format: "iife", 
  platform: "browser",
  minify: true,
  sourcemap: true,
  external: ["react", "react-dom"]
});
```

